  <h4>Content</h4>

  <p>A content modal can include different kinds of information and interactive elements. A basic content modal should include at least a headline, content, a button or a call to action, and a close button.</p>

  {% call components.example(palette='light') %}
    <div class="inline-flex centered">
      <img src="{{ '/assets/modal/modal-style-content.svg' | url }}" alt="Modal style content" style="--inline-img-max-width: 872px;">
    </div>
  {%- endcall %}

  <h4>Video player</h4>

  <p>A video player modal showcases a video at a large size for easy viewing. It includes a video, playback controls, and a close button.</p>

  {% call components.example(palette='light') %}
    <div class="inline-flex centered">
      <img src="{{ '/assets/modal/modal-style-video-player.svg' | url }}" alt="Modal style video player" style="--inline-img-max-width: 872px;">
    </div>
  {%- endcall %}

  <h4>Background overlay</h4>

  <p>The background overlay is a black solid with opacity that is positioned under a modal container. It eliminates distractions and helps a user focus on the content in the modal.</p>

{%- endcall %}

